&lt;h4 id=&quot;budget-options&quot;&gt;Budget Options&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Replace &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;24842&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Superior Rune of the Monk with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;84171&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Superior Rune of Rebirth&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Replace &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;74326&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Superior Sigil of Transference with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;24551&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Superior Sigil of Water&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;small&gt;&lt;em&gt;Note: Weapon swap is optional, all the available options will lock you out of hammer and thus drop your boon coverage. Alternate weapon sets should be prioritised based on utility requirements.&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;consumables&quot;&gt;Consumables&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;91690&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bowl of Fruit Salad with Mint Garnish OR &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;68634&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Delicious Rice Ball &lt;em&gt;(budget alternative)&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;67528&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bountiful Maintenance Oil&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h1 id=&quot;build&quot;&gt;Build&lt;&#x2F;h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Heal Alacrity Build&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;chatlink&quot; class=&quot;language-chatlink z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-chatlink&quot; data-lang=&quot;chatlink&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source z-chatlink&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-begin&quot;&gt;[&amp;amp;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;DQExLS4tQRp&#x2F;ADgBLQEtATYBSAEyATIBcRIAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAABMwAA&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-end&quot;&gt;]&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;div data-armory-embed=&#x27;skills&#x27; data-armory-ids=&#x27;9083,9084,9153,9163,30461&#x27;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;&lt;div data-armory-embed=&#x27;specializations&#x27; data-armory-ids=&#x27;49,46,65&#x27; data-armory-49-traits=&#x27;1899,562,558&#x27; data-armory-46-traits=&#x27;624,587,554&#x27; data-armory-65-traits=&#x27;2190,2210,2195&#x27;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;trait-alternatives&quot;&gt;Trait Alternatives&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;617&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Master of Consecrations if you are taking consecrations.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bring &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;654&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Protector&#x27;s Restoration if there aren&#x27;t blockable mechanics.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;small&gt;&lt;em&gt;This build is a simplified version of the heal alacrity build on &lt;a rel=&quot;noopener&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;snowcrows.com&#x2F;builds&#x2F;raids&#x2F;guardian&#x2F;heal-alacrity-willbender&quot;&gt;snowcrows&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; with selective preferences for lower intensity. If you are able to adapt to the version on SC, feel free to follow their guide.&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;rotation-and-utilities&quot;&gt;Rotation and Utilities&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;heal-alac-rotation&quot;&gt;Heal Alac Rotation&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use your virtues starting from &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62668&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Rushing Justice (F1) -&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62603&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Flowing Resolve (F2) -&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62648&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Crashing Courage (F3).&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Auto Attack with minimal interruptions, using &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9084&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; &quot;Advance!&quot; can provide the group with permanent swiftness without interrupting your autos.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62603&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Flowing Resolve (F2) on cooldown, afterwards use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62668&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Rushing Justice (F1)&#x2F;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62648&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Crashing Courage (F3) to reposition.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9153&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; &quot;Stand Your Ground!&quot; when you require stability.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Burst Heal Spear rotation for Fury (Refer to Burst Heal Section)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;small&gt;&lt;em&gt;The importance of your auto attacks cannot be emphasized enough. Your auto attacks heal, provide alacrity, regeneration, might and protection and a field to trigger Relic of Karakosa with!&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;
&lt;small&gt;&lt;em&gt;You may skip the spear rotation and take &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;29965&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; &quot;Feel My Wrath!&quot; instead.&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;
&lt;small&gt;&lt;em&gt;Some boon DPS classes provide additional fury uptime, freeing your spear rotation for burst healing.&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;burst-heals-and-revives&quot;&gt;Burst Heals and Revives&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;53482&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Glacial Blow (Hammer 2) for burst heals (due to Relic of Karakosa). You may refresh this skill using &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9124&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Banish (Hammer 4).&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9083&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; &quot;Receive the Light!&quot; for a burst heal.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9163&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Mercy as an emergency revive.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Swap to spear -&amp;gt;5,4,3,2,1:
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;73132&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Symbol of Luminance(Spear 5)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;73094&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Solar Storm(Spear 4)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;72978&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Gleaming Disc(Spear 3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;72940&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Helio Rush(Spear 2)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;73055&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Daybreaking Slash(Spear 1 Auto Attack)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Swap back to hammer when ready&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;crowd-control-rotation&quot;&gt;Crowd Control rotation&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You have decent CC by just using &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9124&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Banish (Hammer 4) and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9260&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Zealot&#x27;s Embrace (Hammer 3).&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You can extend your CC rotation by starting with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;53482&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Glacial Blow (Hammer 2) and refreshing it with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9124&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Banish (Hammer 4).&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If you need more CC you may bring &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9128&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Sanctuary, which is ideally used in a precast scenario so you can top it up with Hammer 4.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;hybrid-dps&quot;&gt;Hybrid DPS&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;This build does decent DPS.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For low heal-pressure fights, you may bring more power traits to increase your DPS.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;other-tips-and-tricks&quot;&gt;Other tips and tricks&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You may drop &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9153&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; &quot;Stand Your Ground!&quot; for different utilities.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62648&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Crashing Courage allows you to shadow step through mechanics&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Blocking increases your heal power and doing so intelligently allows efficient use of &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;1899&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Invigorated Bulwark&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;optimisation&quot;&gt;Optimisation&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;raid-ready&quot;&gt;Raid Ready&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W1 Gorseval - Immobilise your spirit with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9151&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Wrath and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9260&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Zealot&#x27;s Embrace (Hammer 3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W1 Sabetha - You can teleport through flame wall with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;62648&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Crashing Courage.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W2 Slothasor - Bring &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;610&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Absolute Resolve for additional condition cleanses.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W2 Matthias - Bring &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9251&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Wall of Reflection for reflects. Bring &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9128&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Sanctuary if you require more CC.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W3 Escort - This build is able to solo towers albeit a little slow with 6-8k dps. If you want to do the JP, bring &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;29965&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; &quot;Feel My Wrath!&quot; for a superspeed boost.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W4 Samarog - You may knock Rigom back with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9124&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Banish (Hammer 4) and immobilise with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9260&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Zealot&#x27;s Embrace (Hammer 3) and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9099&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Chains of Light (Scepter 3). Bring &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9128&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Sanctuary if you require more CC.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W4 Deimos - If you are the healer, due to the low toughness, you will probably be tasked to provide group aegis for the other DPS players.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W6 Conjured Amalgamate - Your power DPS can be quite significant despite being a healer. Do not stop attacking with autos. Place &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9128&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Sanctuary when CA tosses out shields for a precast CC.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W6 Qadim - You want to precast &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9128&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Sanctuary for each CC phase and load the CC bar with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9124&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Banish (Hammer 4) as soon as the minibosses appear.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;W7 Sabir - For the final phase if your group needs projectile blocks, consider &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9182&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Shield of the Avenger and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;9251&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Wall of Reflection&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;small&gt;With the new reduced cooldown, Mace&#x2F;Focus can be an alternate weapon to tank, e.g. to block Deimos comfortably. However there are much better healing&#x2F;tank options out there.&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
